[thinking] **Evaluating class initialization testing**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about a class initialization property test. So, it seems like calling Log.setLog might trigger the static initializer first, executing the default setting. When testing a custom logger, the static initializer happens before setLog, which allows doing this in the same test. But since JUnit runs tests arbitrarily, I need to consider that the first reference to Log could affect behavior. If an unwind test calls Log.setLog first, it could use the defaults, but I’ll have to check Slf4jLog.
