ght have implications for dynamic access at runtime as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing Log Test Coverage**\\n\\nI’m realizing the previous report shows that we may have some uncovered areas from the JVM, perhaps due to the lack of Log tests. That’s good to know! I want to ensure that the configured logger is forced and that `newInstance` succeeds via property settings before loading the Log class. However, I have to be careful not to use the Log class before those settings are applied. I need to strategize on how to effectively test this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7fZGIijuv9Ok8p90kUand9ms|fc_02fcca9fe07af4370169f4f6d095dc81968214cc2d32afe642", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge10/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/main/extracted/org/mortbay/util/Loader.java", "limit": 180}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1422, "output": 927, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18221, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777661635572, "responseId": "resp_02fcca9fe07af4370169f4f6c3ec848196b0dd5b3723cc6d62"}}
